title: Weaver's Thesis Book (Germany), 19th century
creditline: Museum purchase from Friends of the Museum Fund
description: Description and directions for setting up a loom, including sketches of heddle arrangements, and finished samples of 102 different textiles. Directions in German script. Bound in worn grayish buckram with "Fried. Rölker" stamped in gold letters on the front cover.

tombstone.epitaph: Weaver's Thesis Book (Germany), 19th century; buckram, paper; H x W x D: 27 x 41.8 x 4.5 cm (10 5/8 x 16 7/16 x 1 3/4 in.); Museum purchase from Friends of the Museum Fund; 1938-26-2
